      <hedline>
        <hl1>Cell Phone Sacrilege</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Diana Binder letter responds to Sharon White Taylor's July 5 Op-Ed article; condemns insensitivity and thoughtlessness of cell phone users (M)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Wireless and Witless,'' by Sharon White Taylor (Op-Ed, July 5):</p>
        <p>The epitome of insensitivity and thoughtlessness occurred during a  visit to the Museum of Jewish Heritage in Lower Manhattan, in the section dedicated to the Holocaust.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Wireless and Witless,'' by Sharon White Taylor (Op-Ed, July 5):</p>
        <p>The epitome of insensitivity and thoughtlessness occurred during a  visit to the Museum of Jewish Heritage in Lower Manhattan, in the section dedicated to the Holocaust.</p>
        <p>The hushed environment was interrupted when on two separate occasions, in loud voices, two different parties were on their cell phones making dinner plans.</p>
        <p>DIANA BINDER  New York, July 7, 2000</p>
      </block>
